patient was in a RTA, which I think stands for Road Traffic Accident.","dimension":13,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.19534,0.37358,0.070494,0.10307,0.05112,0.060012,0.035227,0.029072,0.02471,0.021242,0.018453,0.017688],"unified_progress":[0.25244,0.14749,0.076037,0.11248,0.075762,0.096692,0.057029,0.049782,0.0429,0.036625,0.030187,0.022567]},{"section":3,"text":"He has a few drops of blood at the external urethral meatus.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.1401,0.22711,0.16582,0.087157,0.071391,0.072391,0.052728,0.060584,0.038005,0.033311,0.027471,0.023936],"unified_progress":[0.11603,0.14924,0.12967,0.094218,0.089619,0.089947,0.071755,0.08393,0.055519,0.048567,0.039738,0.031762]},{"section":4,"text":"So that's a sign of possible urethral injury.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.086117,0.13465,0.13099,0.11495,0.097042,0.086376,0.076778,0.070648,0.061713,0.056792,0.044362,0.039577],"unified_progress":[0.086279,0.095237,0.101,0.10423,0.10051,0.09497,0.088515,0.084238,0.077049,0.069222,0.054569,0.044182]},{"section":5,"text":"Then he hasn't passed urine, and his bladder is palpable.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.10547,0.16957,0.12953,0.096263,0.081246,0.083935,0.069001,0.074243,0.058135,0.050884,0.043637,0.038079],"unified_progress":[0.094133,0.12979,0.10925,0.097974,0.090403,0.088201,0.079299,0.083795,0.070473,0.062057,0.052641,0.041982]},{"section":6,"text":"A palpable bladder suggests that he's unable to void, so there's a distended bladder.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.075842,0.13396,0.12333,0.10384,0.091089,0.09027,0.079211,0.077951,0.072279,0.058495,0.05,0.043734],"unified_progress":[0.070258,0.1024,0.10203,0.10398,0.099057,0.095994,0.087567,0.085608,0.083839,0.066442,0.056417,0.046408]},{"section":7,"text":"Hmm, so the key points here are the mechanism of injury (RTA), hematuria at the urethral meatus, inability to urinate, and a palpable bladder.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.071896,0.11894,0.11127,0.09978,0.091111,0.088808,0.081659,0.080118,0.073906,0.068464,0.059291,0.054755],"unified_progress":[0.075305,0.091483,0.092625,0.095878,0.095369,0.093785,0.089547,0.088345,0.083584,0.075591,0.064542,0.053946]},{"section":8,"text":"I remember that in trauma, especially in males, a straddle injury can cause anterior urethral trauma, but in high-impact accidents like RTA, posterior urethral injuries are more common.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047906,0.087199,0.095831,0.10075,0.10069,0.098847,0.094708,0.088189,0.082932,0.078188,0.065799,0.058961],"unified_progress":[0.059102,0.077663,0.091555,0.096911,0.097953,0.10159,0.095448,0.092075,0.087187,0.079493,0.065921,0.055095]},{"section":9,"text":"Posterior urethral injuries often occur at the membranous part, which is more common in males.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035841,0.075613,0.088298,0.097623,0.10096,0.10181,0.10045,0.092936,0.09156,0.08209,0.069789,0.063021],"unified_progress":[0.049703,0.068255,0.088465,0.098737,0.10236,0.10578,0.099911,0.094619,0.091675,0.078951,0.065589,0.05596]},{"section":10,"text":"When the urethra is disrupted, there's bleeding from the meatus, which they mentioned here.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045743,0.084783,0.090139,0.094553,0.095213,0.096046,0.094999,0.090594,0.090174,0.081114,0.071493,0.065149],"unified_progress":[0.057199,0.075214,0.088213,0.096831,0.1014,0.099893,0.096817,0.092901,0.09022,0.078058,0.066551,0.056707]},{"section":11,"text":"The inability to urinate would lead to urinary retention, hence the distended bladder.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041331,0.080492,0.084938,0.088298,0.091969,0.09572,0.096946,0.094965,0.091303,0.085082,0.078787,0.070168],"unified_progress":[0.053342,0.071221,0.078875,0.084022,0.090749,0.094489,0.09453,0.095656,0.094421,0.089675,0.082946,0.070074]},{"section":12,"text":"The presence of blood at the meatus along with these symptoms is classic for a urethral rupture.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038669,0.076849,0.086785,0.092034,0.092955,0.093499,0.093909,0.090604,0.091674,0.087259,0.079141,0.076623],"unified_progress":[0.044028,0.067091,0.080489,0.089856,0.094784,0.096818,0.09626,0.094163,0.094912,0.089219,0.080577,0.071802]},{"section":13,"text":"Another possibility could be a bladder injury, but bladder injuries from trauma might present with more significant hematuria and maybe pelvic fractures.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028719,0.065043,0.078686,0.088121,0.094141,0.097878,0.1014,0.099774,0.098436,0.093971,0.08456,0.069266],"unified_progress":[0.032286,0.061095,0.07791,0.088616,0.096279,0.10055,0.10117,0.10145,0.10031,0.097455,0.081627,0.061251]},{"section":14,"text":"But the key here is the blood at the urethral meatus.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033318,0.067723,0.077902,0.08478,0.089063,0.093082,0.095475,0.095023,0.098418,0.093734,0.089437,0.082045],"unified_progress":[0.040345,0.061402,0.074559,0.084884,0.092461,0.096545,0.097749,0.098032,0.099786,0.094686,0.086605,0.072946]},{"section":15,"text":"Also, with a posterior urethral injury, there's often associated pelvic fracture, which might not be mentioned here, but the RTA could involve that.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030805,0.067388,0.079682,0.088022,0.09248,0.097724,0.098526,0.096792,0.099738,0.092253,0.083723,0.072866],"unified_progress":[0.051366,0.074306,0.083085,0.090725,0.09542,0.095988,0.09587,0.094985,0.09436,0.086865,0.075154,0.061875]},{"section":16,"text":"Wait, the question doesn't mention a pelvic fracture, but maybe it's implied.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0302,0.060406,0.075021,0.083981,0.0927,0.097833,0.099148,0.099833,0.10017,0.095032,0.088537,0.077136],"unified_progress":[0.049342,0.077688,0.084938,0.096063,0.095366,0.091697,0.095911,0.092063,0.087712,0.094389,0.075363,0.059468]},{"section":17,"text":"Even without that, the combination of blood at the meatus and inability to void points more towards urethral injury.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034607,0.066884,0.076413,0.083527,0.088005,0.091202,0.09419,0.094118,0.096228,0.094952,0.090239,0.089633],"unified_progress":[0.046385,0.062911,0.075742,0.087703,0.090505,0.092998,0.093973,0.0938,0.094391,0.092515,0.08744,0.081637]},{"section":18,"text":"So the most likely diagnosis here is a posterior urethral rupture.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026554,0.052063,0.061426,0.06858,0.074333,0.079686,0.085475,0.088583,0.097092,0.098336,0.1083,0.15957],"unified_progress":[0.027655,0.040531,0.051373,0.062145,0.066658,0.076075,0.079436,0.088378,0.098898,0.10336,0.13307,0.17242]},{"section":19,"text":"Alternatively, anterior urethral injury, but given the mechanism, posterior is more likely in RTA.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023824,0.051703,0.063109,0.072188,0.08019,0.087214,0.093784,0.097478,0.10257,0.10369,0.10525,0.119],"unified_progress":[0.032231,0.046159,0.056604,0.06588,0.07284,0.080479,0.084786,0.094147,0.10095,0.10737,0.11936,0.1392]},{"section":20,"text":"So putting it all together, the diagnosis should be posterior urethral rupture.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029764,0.049655,0.054285,0.060819,0.067901,0.074785,0.082309,0.088391,0.097676,0.10242,0.11534,0.17665],"unified_progress":[0.032506,0.03286,0.040024,0.048717,0.054403,0.064459,0.070105,0.082769,0.095437,0.10774,0.15144,0.21954]}]}}